<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-09-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-09-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="181" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d181">
                            <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Conger</persName> to
                                        <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.—Received October
                                    1, 1900.]</seg></opener>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Pekin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-09-29"><hi rend="italic">September 29,
                                        1900</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                            <p>(Mr. Conger reports that the Russian legation has to-day been removed
                                to Tientsin.)</p>
